    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="314"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                <head>314. Central Intelligence Agency Information Cable<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d314fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency, <gloss
                            target="#t_DDO_1">DDO</gloss> Files, Job 89–00176R, Box 1, Folder 19,
                        Political Activities—Iran. Secret; Security Information. Sent to the
                        Departments of State, Army, Navy, and Air Force, the National Security
                        Agency, the Joint Chiefs of Staff, the Secretary of Defense, the Office of
                        National Estimates, and the Office of Current Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <idno type="document-identifier">CS PD 916</idno>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-08"
                        >September 8, 1953</date>.</dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Qashqai–Zahedi Relations</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <head>SOURCE</head>
                    <item>[<hi rend="italic">2 lines not declassified</hi>]</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <head>SUPPLEMENT TO</head>
                    <item>CS–19535 (PD–871)<note n="2" xml:id="d314fn2">Not found.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>1. The <persName corresp="#p_QKK_1">Qashqai Khans</persName> are attempting to
                    obtain from the <persName corresp="#p_ZA_1">Zahedi</persName> government some
                    “face saving” concessions (possibly a public announcement that the government
                    has no intention of arresting “loyal Iranians” Khosro and <persName
                        corresp="#p_QMH_1">Mohammad Hoseyn Qashqai</persName>, and that it has re<pb
                        facs="0791" n="754" xml:id="pg_754"/>leased fellow members of the former
                    national movement fractions who were formerly arrested before burying the
                    hatchet with Zahedi.</p>
                <p>2. At the request of the Qashqai, <persName corresp="#p_ZA_1">Zahedi</persName>
                    is sending Hoseyn Makki to Shiraz on 3 September to confer with <persName
                        corresp="#p_QMNK_1">Nasr Qashqai</persName>. (Washington comment: For
                    further information concerning Makki’s activities, see PD–903.)<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d314fn3">Not found.</note>
                </p>
                <p>3. The Qashqai have absolutely no intention of rebelling or “seceding” and will
                    fight only in self-defense if attacked by the army.</p>
                <p>Field distribution: State, Army, SUBCOMNELM formal <gloss target="#t_dissem_1"
                        >dissem</gloss> follows. (End of message)</p>
                <p>The above info based on Tehe 868 (IN 16169).<note n="4" xml:id="d314fn4">Not
                        found.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
